<br>
reminds me of something common in chess.  amateurs make bad moves just to feel like they are doing something.  thats one of the reasons amateurs dont draw as much.  they play to loose eventually because it gives them some sense of control.<br>
<br>
whats my point?<br>
<br>
are we really making our position safer by going at iraq by atogonizing north korea by aligning china and n korea as allies in our rhetoric?<br>
<br>
prolly not.  <br>
<br>
i mean consider the logic of this move on iraq.<br>
<br>
we claim as an executive branch that iraq has weapons of mass destruction.  we claim that.   <br>
<br>
now assuming thats true. we obviously dont know where they are.  if we did know where these weapons of mass destructions are at then we would have the weapons inspectors on them in 2 seconds.<br>
<br>
we claim iraq has weapons of mass destruction.<br>
we dont know where they are.<br>
when we do go in there with troops what happens to them.<br>
<br>
the fear on this thread was &quot;ohhh poor isreal&quot;<br>
thats not the appropriate fear.  the real fear should be poor cleveland.  poor san francisco.<br>
<br>
because if we dont know where they are in iraq what makes you sure we can stop a peanut butter jar in a thermous from leaving iraq?   isreal.  nooooo.  US  yes.<br>
<br>
<br>
So we're back to the wisdom from chess.  when people dont know what to do they play the most active looking thing.  in this case we are destabilizing the whole mess.  im not saying we are making ourselves LESS safe by attack iraq.  im saying we are NOT making ourselves safer.  basically im saying we are wasting alot of effort and the end result will be the same world.  the same US  the same problems.  the move does nothing.<br>
<br>
<br>
We have done well as a country to avoid terrorism.  empirically.   Why the knee jerk reaction?  We lost a piece but that doesnt mean our play was wrong.  We lost people in New York but what if we had it to do different?  Do you know that if the US had been more aggressive more isolated less respectful of internal rights then we would have lost less people?<br>
<br>
you dont know that.  hell i dont even think that?  so why the change of tone?  Why the war on terror when the components of the war on terror would have resulted most likely if implemented in 1970 in more then just two US buildings gone.   <br>
<br>
moving to move. its stupid.  its funny in chess afterwards.  its a riot to look back and go gah why didnt i just see that i could have stayed calm.  but in real life.   ITS NOT FUNNY.<br>
